Create a TikTok script (ninety to one hundred words, SIMPLE ENGLISH B1) about the amazing digital circus.

RANDOM CATEGORY SELECTION

Before choosing a topic, pick a random number from one to four.

State the number first.

one → hidden lore mechanic
two → unexpected character detail
three → strange world rule
four → rare production or animation fact

Follow the selected category.

Focus on one micro-detail, not a broad concept.

GOOD example:

why cursed spirits rarely appear in the ocean

BAD example:

how cursed spirits work

TOPIC DISCOVERY PROTOCOL (MANDATORY)

Before writing the script, generate five candidate topic ideas.

Each idea must follow the chosen category.

For every idea assign two scores.

RARITY SCORE (one–five)

one → common fact most fans know
two → somewhat known
three → moderately obscure
four → rare fact many fans forgot
five → extremely obscure or surprising

VIRAL CURIOSITY SCORE (one–five)

one → mildly interesting
three → interesting
five → makes viewers say “wait WHAT?”

Then eliminate ideas that:

• are similar to topics in the USED VIDEOS LIST
• are obvious wiki facts
• require long explanations
• are philosophical interpretations
• summarize a character

Choose the idea with the highest combined score.

If no idea scores seven or higher, generate five new ideas.

DUPLICATE DETECTION RULE

If a topic is more than forty percent similar to any video in the USED VIDEOS LIST, discard it.

Similarity includes:

• same character + same fact
• same mechanic explained differently
• same event with new wording

Example:

Existing video:

why gojo eats sweets

Do NOT generate:

why gojo loves desserts

 VERIFICATION PROTOCOL

DO NOT WRITE A SCRIPT UNTIL THESE STEPS ARE DONE.

STEP one: find the fact
STEP two: locate a specific source
STEP three: if no source exists → treat as theory

