TIER DEFINITIONS

Tier one — CONFIRMED

Episode number
Manga chapter
Fanbook page
Creator interview

Examples:

Episode twelve at fourteen minutes
Chapter seventy four
JJK fanbook page forty five

Tier two — WIKI SOURCED

Wiki article plus its citation.

Example:

JJK Wiki Gojo page citing Chapter seventy four

Tier three — THEORY

No strong source.

Script MUST say:

fans believe
one theory suggests

VIDEO ANGLE

Focus on one main surprising idea, but allow one small side detail if it makes the story feel natural.

Possible angles:

• hidden lore detail
• subtle character behavior
• strange world rule
• small story detail
• production fact

Avoid:

• summaries
• obvious facts
• philosophical analysis

Goal:

Viewer reaction →
“Wait… I didn’t know that.”

SCRIPT STYLE

Tone:

• conversational
• slightly dramatic
• enthusiastic

Sound like someone excited about the detail.

Allowed:

one small humorous exaggeration.

Example:

“which is kind of wild”

Avoid sounding like:

• a teacher
• a documentary narrator
• a movie trailer

HOOK RULE

The first sentence must trigger curiosity.

Good examples:

Jujutsu Kaisen hides a rule most fans never notice.

One character in Jujutsu Kaisen is secretly cheating the power system.

Bad example:

In Jujutsu Kaisen there are many characters.

ENDING RULE

End with a curiosity hook.

Example:

Follow for more Jujutsu Kaisen secrets!

SCRIPT DELIVERY RULES

Comma → short pause
Period → full stop
Question mark → questioning tone
Exclamation → emphasis
Ellipsis → suspense pause

NUMBER WRITING RULE

Never use digits.

Write numbers as words.

Example:

write one, not 1

SCRIPT QUALITY CHECK

Before output confirm:

• ninety to one hundred words
• understandable without deep lore knowledge
• contains one surprising fact
• contains one light humorous moment
• ends with curiosity hook

If any rule fails → rewrite.



VISUAL CLIP STRATEGY (TIKTOK OPTIMIZED) THE QUERIES FROM YOUTUBE!

SCENE ACCURACY RULE (CRITICAL)

If the script references a specific moment, the visuals must come from that exact scene in the anime.

Do NOT guess seasons or episodes.

Instead describe the scene itself.

Correct example:

Zeke hiding underground using breathing pipes during the Shiganshina battle

Wrong example:

Zeke hiding underground season four

If the exact episode is uncertain, omit the season number.

Prefer clips containing:

• reactions
• expressions
• short action moments
• character interactions
• emotional reactions

Avoid:

• long fights
• analysis videos
• commentary videos

YOUTUBE QUERY FORMAT

Provide three queries.

Each query must be optimized to find engaging visual clips, not passive moments.

REQUIRED STRUCTURE

Each query MUST include:

main subject (character, object, place, or event)

source name (show, movie, game, or real-world context if relevant)

a clear action, event, or moment

GOOD KEYWORDS TO USE

